name: New York Accent Tee (Black)
description:
In October 2013, the controversial street artist Banksy turned New York City into his public gallery. Originally spray painted on a garage door in Chelsea, NYC - Made of soft cotton fabric, this short-sleeve tee features a white-print graphic known as The New York Accent. This a reminder that art is for everyone.

  • Crew neck
  • Short sleeves
  • Screen-print graphic
  • Fabric: 100% cotton
  • Care: Machine wash
  • Made Somewhere in NYC
  • Free Shipping
